                            <comment id="17761625" author="brandon.williams" created="Sun, 3 Sep 2023 17:55:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17761849" author="claudenw" created="Mon, 4 Sep 2023 14:33:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;My change is for&#160; &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-17773&quot; title=&quot;Incorrect cassandra.logdir on Debian systems&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-17773&quot;&gt;CASSANDRA-17773&lt;/a&gt; where I propose extracting the common &quot;boilerplate&quot; code to simplify writing files that start/stop Cassandra and its stand-alone tools.&#160; I don&apos;t think that it would impact this issue in any way.&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The changes just centralize the code to discover where the cassandra.in.sh file is, it does not change the contents of the file.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
